🔧 Popular Mechanical Engineering Design Software
SolidWorks – 3D CAD modeling, assemblies, simulation; widely used for product design and prototyping.

AutoCAD – Industry standard for 2D drafting and mechanical drawings.

CATIA – Advanced design tool for aerospace and automotive industries; excellent for complex assemblies.

PTC Creo – Strong in parametric modeling, simulation, and industrial-scale design.

Siemens NX – High-end CAD/CAM/CAE integration; powerful for manufacturing workflows.

Fusion 360 – Cloud-based CAD/CAM tool; popular among startups and small teams for collaboration.

ANSYS – Leading software for simulation, finite element analysis (FEA), and computational fluid dynamics (CFD).

MATLAB/Simulink – Used for modeling, control systems, and simulation in mechanical and mechatronic engineering.

Inventor (Autodesk) – 3D mechanical design with strong integration to AutoCAD.

COMSOL Multiphysics – Specialized in multiphysics simulations (thermal, structural, fluid, etc.).
